It&#8217;s believed the Benoni man and his friends were driving in their car on Saturday night when three suspects opened fire. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police say they are investigating a case of murder and attempted murder after a 21-year-old was killed and his friend wounded in Fordsburg in Johannesburg.It s believed the man from Benoni and a group of his friends were driving in their car on Saturday night when three suspects opened fire before fleeing the scene.Police spokesperson Mavela Masondo say the deceased was certified dead at the scene and the other victim was taken to hospital in a serious condition.Masondo is calling upon the community to come forward with the information that can lead to the arrest of the suspect. The motive for the shooting is not known at the moment and we have launched a manhunt for the suspects. We are investigating a case of murder and attempted murder. 